      "content": "i get that but i'm really looking for more specifics. like if i do turn the power off, what exactly should i be looking for to see if the capacitor is blown? is there a specific way it looks when it's broken? i'm not trying to fix the whole thing, i just want to know if it's a cheap part i can swap or if it's something way more complicated.",
